# AVD-AWS-0057: iac/aws/analytics.tf, aws_iam_role_policy.miner_results,
# s3:PutObject on "<results-bucket-arn>/results/*".
#
# The miner writes one dynamically-named object per judged case
# (results/dt=YYYY-MM-DD/<sweep_id>/<case_id>.json) — there is no way to
# enumerate object keys ahead of time in an IAM policy, so a prefix-scoped
# Resource ARN (trailing /*) is the tightest grant possible for "can write
# any object under this prefix." This is standard practice for write access
# to a dynamic keyspace, not an actual wildcard-permission gap.
#
# The other historical instance of this rule (kms:GenerateDataKey on "*")
# was fixed directly by scoping to a dedicated CMK (aws_kms_key.results) —
# see analytics.tf. This ignore only still matches the s3:PutObject case.
AVD-AWS-0057
